&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;North West Ipswich Practices &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(Chesterfield Drive, Deben Road and Norwich Road)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Telephonist/Care Navigator posts available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deben Road – 1 post @ 22 hours per week:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monday 1pm – 6.30pm (5.5 hours)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tuesday 8am – 1.30pm (5.5 hours)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thursday 1.30pm – 6.30pm (5 hours)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Friday 8am – 2pm (6 hours)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Norwich Road – 2 posts @ 20 hours per week:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post 1 – Monday &amp; Friday 8am – 6.30pm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post 2 – Thursday &amp; Friday 8am – 6.30pm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rate of pay £9.30ph&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chesterfield Drive, Deben Road and Norwich Road practices are 3 of 13 practices in Suffolk who are part of Suffolk Primary Care. We are actively developing our collaborative working agenda with a view to delivering shared services to all our 30,000+ patients. This includes operating a shared acute/same day service from Deben Road and routine/non-urgent care from Norwich Road and Chesterfield Drive. There are also plans for Chesterfield Drive and Deben Road practices to relocate to a new purpose built premises on the former ‘Tooks Bakery’ site in late 2022/early 2023. If you want to be part of this exciting future, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, experienced and team focused individuals to join our admin teams working at Deben Road and Norwich Road Practices in Ipswich.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to demonstrate excellent communication skills, have the ability to remain calm under pressure and be able to multi-task whilst dealing with frequent interruptions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be able to explain sensitive or complicated information in a clear, sympathetic way that is easily understood.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of working within a GP practice environment and a working knowledge of SystmOne would be a definite advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A DBS check will be undertaken on the successful applicant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: Friday 13th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview dates:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deben Road post – Monday 23rd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Norwich Road posts – Tuesday 1st December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
